{"ts": "2026-06-08T03:57:11.185347+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## App Bootstrap, Routing, and Layout Rendering — Full Flow\n\n### 1. Entry Point: `index.html`\n\nThe browser loads `index.html`, which contains a mount point `<div id=\"app\"></div>` and a module script tag that loads `/src/main.js`:\n\n```html\n<div id=\"app\"></div>\n<script type=\"module\" src=\"/src/main.js\"></script>\n```\n\nVite transforms and serves this ES module, kicking off the Vue application.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Application Bootstrap: `src/main.js`\n\n```js\nimport { createPinia } from 'pinia'\nimport { createApp } from 'vue'\nimport Default from '@/layouts/default/Default.vue'\nimport App from './App.vue'\nimport { router } from './router'\n\nconst app = createApp(App)\n\napp.component('LayoutDefault', Default)   // (1) Register layout globally\napp.use(createPinia())                     // (2) Install Pinia state management\napp.use(router)                            // (3) Install Vue Router\n\napp.mount('#app')                          // (4) Mount to DOM\n```\n\n**Step-by-step:**\n\n1. **`createApp(App)`** — Creates a Vue 3 application instance with `App.vue` as the root component.\n2. **`app.component('LayoutDefault', Default)`** — Registers the `Default.vue` layout component globally under the kebab-case name `LayoutDefault`. This is the key to the dynamic layout system.\n3. **`app.use(createPinia())`** — Installs Pinia (state management) before the router so stores are available to route guards/components.\n4. **`app.use(router)`** — Installs the Vue Router plugin, making `$router` and `$route` available in all components and enabling `<RouterView>`.\n5. **`app.mount('#app')`** — Mounts the application onto the `#app` div, triggering the initial render.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Root Component & Dynamic Layout Resolution: `src/App.vue`\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <component :is=\"layout\">\n    <RouterView />\n  </component>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nexport default {\n  name: 'App',\n  computed: {\n    layout() {\n      return `layout-${this.$route.meta.layout || 'default'}`\n    },\n  },\n}\n</script>\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n\n- `App.vue` renders a **dynamic component** via `<component :is=\"layout\">`. The `is` attribute binds to a computed property `layout`.\n- The `layout` computed reads `this.$route.meta.layout` from the current route. For every route defined in the router, `meta.layout` is set to `'default'`, so the computed returns the string `'layout-default'`.\n- Because `main.js` registered the layout component as `'LayoutDefault'` (which Vue normalizes to `'layout-default'` in kebab-case resolution), the dynamic component `<component :is=\"'layout-default'\">` resolves to the globally registered `Default.vue` layout.\n- Inside the layout, `<RouterView />` is passed as the **default slot content**. The layout component renders this slot wherever `<slot />` appears.\n\nThis pattern means:\n- Different routes can specify different layouts by setting `meta.layout` (e.g., `'empty'`, `'admin'`).\n- The layout is swapped dynamically based on the active route without re-mounting the entire app.\n\n---\n\n### 4. The Default Layout: `src/layouts/default/Default.vue`\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\nThe default layout is a **shell template**:\n- `<DefaultNav />` — A Bootstrap navbar with `<RouterLink>` links to Home (`/`) and About (`/about`).\n- `<slot />` — The outlet where `<RouterView />` (the matched route component) is injected.\n- `<DefaultFooter />` — A sticky footer.\n\nThis means every route using the `'default'` layout gets the same nav and footer wrapped around its view.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Router Configuration: `src/router/index.js`\n\n```js\nimport { createRouter, createWebHashHistory } from 'vue-router'\nimport Home from '../views/Home.vue'\n\nconst history = createWebHashHistory()\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,                          // eagerly imported\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    component: () => import('../views/About.vue'),  // lazy-loaded!\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n]\n\nconst router = createRouter({\n  linkActiveClass: 'active',\n  history,\n  routes,\n})\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Uses **hash-mode history** (`createWebHashHistory`) — URLs look like `/#/about`.\n- The **Home** route (`/`) eagerly imports `Home.vue` — it's included in the initial bundle.\n- The **About** route (`/about`) uses a **dynamic `import()`** — this enables **route-level code splitting**. Vite generates a separate chunk (`about.[hash].js`) that is **lazy-loaded** only when the user navigates to `/about`.\n- Both routes set `meta.layout: 'default'`, so they both use the `Default` layout.\n\n---\n\n### 6. How the About Page Is Loaded — End-to-End Flow\n\n#### Initial Load (no About yet)\nWhen the app first loads (e.g., at `/#/`):\n1. `main.js` → `createApp(App)` → router installed → `app.mount('#app')`.\n2. Vue Router matches the initial route `/` to the **Home** component (eagerly imported, already in the bundle).\n3. `App.vue` computes `layout = 'layout-default'`, renders `<Default>` with `Home` view inside `<slot>`.\n4. The `About.vue` chunk is **not downloaded yet**.\n\n#### Navigating to About\nWhen the user clicks the \"About\" link in `DefaultNav` (a `<RouterLink to=\"/about\">`), or the URL hash changes to `/#/about`:\n\n1. **Vue Router** detects the route change to `/about`.\n2. It finds the matching route record — the About route.\n3. **Code splitting kicks in:** The dynamic import `() => import('../views/About.vue')` triggers a network request for the lazy chunk (`about.[hash].js`).\n4. While the chunk loads, Vue Router can show a loading state (or the previous view remains visible since there's no global loading guard configured here).\n5. Once the chunk is fetched and parsed, the `About` component definition is resolved.\n6. **`App.vue` re-computes** — `layout` is still `'layout-default'` (since `meta.layout` is `'default'`), so the same `Default` layout shell stays mounted.\n7. **`<RouterView />` swaps** — the previous `Home` component is unmounted, and the newly resolved `About` component is mounted inside the layout's `<slot />`.\n8. The user sees the About page content (`\"This is the about page\"`) wrapped in the same navbar and footer.\n\n#### Key architectural properties:\n- **The layout never remounts** during same-layout navigation — only `<RouterView>` content changes. This preserves navbar state (e.g., the mobile hamburger toggle state).\n- **Code splitting is transparent** — Vite + Vue Router handle the async component resolution. The developer simply uses a dynamic `import()` function as the route's `component`.\n- **No extra bootstrapping** is needed for the About page — it piggybacks on the already-initialized Pinia stores, router, and globally registered layout component.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Diagram\n\n```\nindex.html\n  └─ <div id=\"app\">\n       └─ main.js\n            ├─ createApp(App)\n            ├─ register LayoutDefault globally\n            ├─ install Pinia\n            ├─ install Router\n            └─ mount('#app')\n                 └─ App.vue\n                      └─ <component :is=\"layout\">   ← 'layout-default'\n                           └─ Default.vue\n                                ├─ <DefaultNav />    ← RouterLinks\n                                ├─ <slot>            ← <RouterView />\n                                │    └─ Home.vue  OR  About.vue (lazy)\n                                └─ <DefaultFooter />\n```\n\nThe About page is just a lazy-loaded Vue component that drops into this pre-existing shell — no separate bootstrap, no layout remount, just a dynamic import resolved at navigation time.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1997, "prompt_tokens": 9071, "total_tokens": 11068, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 110, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8448}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8448, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 623}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "50f743df-b0b6-42ea-9e78-48c57aa21ac3", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea560-0c5e-72a1-a204-56d77fb5ab8e-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9071, "output_tokens": 1997, "total_tokens": 11068, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8448}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 110}}}}]}}}
